      "id": "PopularPost99799",
      "post_content": "Kitsune:  \n  \nI think you do. Even as you play the card as written, with no errata from newer Oracle wordings, it's still considered a mono artifact, which by the rules of the game (including current) requires you to tap it to activate its ability. \"Mono Artifact\" might not mean anything to us nowadays, but its still relevant, as it takes the place of the tap symbol on this card (and others like it), and still count as \"the way the card is written\", errata or no.",
      "posted_by": "Lateralis0ne",
